weight.\n\nALTER TABLE memory_relations ADD COLUMN note   TEXT;\nALTER TABLE memory_relations ADD COLUMN weight REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 1.0\n  CHECK(weight BETWEEN 0.0 AND 1.0);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":7,"totalLines":7,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/018_relation_semantics.sql","time":{"start":1780925315989,"end":1780925316002}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4a8819193d7410369966778"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbb92001s3Z9Ed2LQQc6Q1","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316006,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0JiOtxlMf9B7ajLvTXf6adNI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: -- Migration 004: Graph reasoning convenience view\n2: -- Creates a view of conflicting memory pairs for quick inspection.\n3: -- No new tables needed — all data already lives in memory_relations.\n4: \n5: CREATE VIEW IF NOT EXISTS memory_conflict_pairs AS\n6:   SELECT\n7:     r.source_memory_id,\n8:     r.target_memory_id,\n9:     r.relationship_type,\n10:     r.created_at,\n11:     a.content AS source_content,\n12:     b.content AS target_content,\n13:     a.category AS source_category,\n14:     b.category AS target_category\n15:   FROM memory_relations r\n16:   JOIN memories a ON a.id = r.source_memory_id\n17:   JOIN memories b ON b.id = r.target_memory_id\n18:   WHERE r.relationship_type IN ('contradicts', 'supersedes');\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/AGENTS.md\n# OpenLTM — agent instructions\n\nHost-agnostic guidance for any AI coding agent working in this repo (Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md`; OpenCode and other tools read this file). OpenLTM gives agents persistent semantic memory across sessions via a local SQLite database.\n\n## Using memory\n\nThe memory tools are exposed over MCP as `recall`, `learn`, `context`, `forget`, `relate` (in Claude Code, prefixed `mcp__plugin_openltm_memory__*`). The goal is automatic knowledge retrieval and capture — use judgment, not a call before every sentence.\n\n- **`recall`** before a non-trivial task, or when the work touches past decisions or an unfamiliar area. Skip for trivial one-liners.\n- **`learn`** after discovering a non-obvious pattern, architectural decision, or gotcha worth keeping across sessions.\n- **`context`** at session start or when switching projects, to restore goals, decisions, and gotchas.\n\nCategories: `preference | architecture | gotcha | pattern | workflow | constraint`. Importance `5` never decays; everything else ages out as it goes unused.\n\n## Working in this repo\n\n- **Runtime is Bun**, not npm/node. Use `bun`, `bunx`, `bun test`.\n- **Tests + typecheck must pass**: `bun test && bun run typecheck`.\n- **Version bumps are mandatory** on any change — `bun run bump <version>` then `bun run verify-version` (it gates all version sources: `package.json`, `.claude-plugin/plugin.json`, `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`, every `packages/*/package.json`, and the README badge).\n- **No secrets, no database files** in commits. `data/*.db*` is gitignored; keep it that way.\n\n## Shipping to OpenCode\n\nInstalling OpenLTM into OpenCode (`bunx @rohirik/openltm-core --opencode`) does two things: registers the `@rohirik/opencode-ltm` plugin in `opencode.json`, and deploys the bundled customization (agents, skills, plugins) from the package's `assets/opencode/` into the user's OpenCode config directory.\n\n## Releasing\n\nTag-driven and tokenless: bump versions, add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry, then `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin main vX.Y.Z`. The tag fires the Release and Publish workflows; npm packages publish via OIDC trusted publishing with provenance — no stored token. Full detail in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n\n## Docs\n\nUser-facing docs are in [`docs/`](docs/README.md); internal design specs in [`docs/internal/`](docs/internal/README.md).\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"-- Migration 004: Graph reasoning convenience view\n-- Creates a view of conflicting memory pairs for quick inspection.\n-- No new tables needed — all data already lives in memory_relations.\n\nCREATE VIEW IF NOT EXISTS memory_conflict_pairs AS\n  SELECT\n    r.source_memory_id,\n    r.target_memory_id,\n    r.relationship_type,\n    r.created_at,\n    a.content AS source_content,\n    b.content AS target_content,\n    a.category AS source_category,\n    b.category AS target_category\n  FROM memory_relations r\n  JOIN memories a ON a.id = r.source_memory_id\n  JOIN memories b ON b.id = r.target_memory_id\n  WHERE r.relationship_type IN ('contradicts', 'supersedes');","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/AGENTS.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql","text":"-- Migration 004: Graph reasoning convenience view\n-- Creates a view of conflicting memory pairs for quick inspection.\n-- No new tables needed — all data already lives in memory_relations.\n\nCREATE VIEW IF NOT EXISTS memory_conflict_pairs AS\n  SELECT\n    r.source_memory_id,\n    r.target_memory_id,\n    r.relationship_type,\n    r.created_at,\n    a.content AS source_content,\n    b.content AS target_content,\n    a.category AS source_category,\n    b.category AS target_category\n  FROM memory_relations r\n  JOIN memories a ON a.id = r.source_memory_id\n  JOIN memories b ON b.id = r.target_memory_id\n  WHERE r.relationship_type IN ('contradicts', 'supersedes');","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":18,"totalLines":18,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql","time":{"start":1780925315985,"end":1780925316004}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4a0819192769d02d9e5cf69"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbb900010FZqdK6vP1XXDb","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316006,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_07dqcVg0bzfcup97PbZli4sk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * graph.ts — Graph traversal engine for LTM reasoning.\n3:  * BFS from a seed memory, up to configurable depth.\n4:  * Detects conflicts, reinforcements, and infers implicit edges via LLM.\n5:  */\n6: import type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\n7: import { getDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\n8: import type { Memory, RelationshipType } from \"./db.js\";\n9: \n10: export interface MemoryNode {\n11:   id: number;\n12:   content: string;\n13:   category: string;\n14:   importance: number;\n15:   project_scope: string | null;\n16: }\n17: \n18: export interface MemoryPair {\n19:   a: MemoryNode;\n20:   b: MemoryNode;\n21:   type: RelationshipType;\n22: }\n23: \n24: export interface InferredRelation {\n25:   a: MemoryNode;\n26:   b: MemoryNode;\n27:   type: RelationshipType;\n28:   persisted: boolean;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export interface TraversalResult {\n32:   chain: MemoryNode[];\n33:   conflicts: MemoryPair[];\n34:   reinforcements: MemoryPair[];\n35:   clusters: MemoryNode[][];\n36:   inferred: InferredRelation[];\n37: }\n38: \n39: const CONFLICT_TYPES = new Set<RelationshipType>([\"contradicts\", \"supersedes\"]);\n40: const REINFORCE_TYPES = new Set<RelationshipType>([\"supports\", \"refines\"]);\n41: \n42: function edgeKey(a: number, b: number): string {\n43:   return `${Math.min(a, b)}:${Math.max(a, b)}`;\n44: }\n45: \n46: interface EdgeRow {\n47:   neighbor_id: number;\n48:   relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n49: }\n50: \n51: function getNeighbors(db: Database, id: number): EdgeRow[] {\n52:   return db.query<EdgeRow, [number, number]>(\n53:     `SELECT target_memory_id as neighbor_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE source_memory_id=?\n54:      UNION ALL\n55:      SELECT source_memory_id as neighbor_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE target_memory_id=?`\n56:   ).all(id, id);\n57: }\n58: \n59: function getMemoryNode(db: Database, id: number): MemoryNode | null {\n60:   return db.query<MemoryNode, [number]>(\n61:     `SELECT id, content, category, importance, project_scope FROM memories WHERE id=? AND status='active'`\n62:   ).get(id) ?? null;\n63: }\n64: \n65: /**\n66:  * BFS traversal from startId up to depth hops.\n67:  * Returns ordered chain (BFS order), plus pairs classified by edge type.\n68:  */\n69: export async function traverseGraph(\n70:   startId: number,\n71:   depth = 2,\n72:   inferImplicit = false,\n73: ): Promise<TraversalResult> {\n74:   const db = getDb();\n75: \n76:   const seedNode = getMemoryNode(db, startId);\n77:   if (!seedNode) {\n78:     return { chain: [], conflicts: [], reinforcements: [], clusters: [], inferred: [] };\n79:   }\n80: \n81:   const visited = new Set<number>([startId]);\n82:   const chain: MemoryNode[] = [seedNode];\n83:   const conflicts: MemoryPair[] = [];\n84:   const reinforcements: MemoryPair[] = [];\n85: \n86:   // BFS queue: [nodeId, depth]\n87:   const queue: Array<[number, number]> = [[startId, 0]];\n88: \n89:   const edgeMap = new Map<string, RelationshipType>(); // \"a:b\" -> type\n90: \n91:   while (queue.length > 0) {\n92:     const [curId, curDepth] = queue.shift()!;\n93:     if (curDepth >= depth) continue;\n94: \n95:     const curNode = getMemoryNode(db, curId);\n96:     if (!curNode) continue;\n97: \n98:     const neighbors = getNeighbors(db, curId);\n99:     for (const edge of neighbors) {\n100:       const neighborNode = getMemoryNode(db, edge.neighbor_id);\n101:       if (!neighborNode) continue;\n102: \n103:       edgeMap.set(edgeKey(curId, edge.neighbor_id), edge.relationship_type);\n104: \n105:       if (CONFLICT_TYPES.has(edge.relationship_type)) {\n106:         conflicts.push({ a: curNode, b: neighborNode, type: edge.relationship_type });\n107:       } else if (REINFORCE_TYPES.has(edge.relationship_type)) {\n108:         reinforcements.push({ a: curNode, b: neighborNode, type: edge.relationship_type });\n109:       }\n110: \n111:       if (!visited.has(edge.neighbor_id)) {\n112:         visited.add(edge.neighbor_id);\n113:         chain.push(neighborNode);\n114:         queue.push([edge.neighbor_id, curDepth + 1]);\n115:       }\n116:     }\n117:   }\n118: \n119:   // Build connected components (clusters) from visited nodes\n120:   const clusters = buildClusters(db, [...visited]);\n121: \n122:   // Optionally infer implicit edges between visited nodes that lack a direct edge\n123:   const inferred: InferredRelation[] = [];\n124:   if (inferImplicit && chain.length >= 2) {\n125:     const { classifyRelation } = await import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n126:     const { relate } = await import(\"./db.js\");\n127: \n128:     const pairs = getPairsWithoutEdge(chain, edgeMap);\n129:     const results = await Promise.allSettled(\n130:       pairs.map(async ([a, b]) => {\n131:         const relType = await classifyRelation(a.content, b.content);\n132:         if (!relType) return null;\n133: \n134:         let persisted = false;\n135:         try {\n136:           relate({ source_id: a.id, target_id: b.id, relationship_type: relType });\n137:           persisted = true;\n138:         } catch {\n139:           // Memory deleted between traversal and relate — ignore\n140:         }\n141: \n142:         return { a, b, type: relType as RelationshipType, persisted };\n143:       })\n144:     );\n145: \n146:     for (const r of results) {\n147:       if (r.status === \"fulfilled\" && r.value) {\n148:         inferred.push(r.value);\n149:         if (CONFLICT_TYPES.has(r.value.type)) {\n150:           conflicts.push({ a: r.value.a, b: r.value.b, type: r.value.type });\n151:         } else if (REINFORCE_TYPES.has(r.value.type)) {\n152:           reinforcements.push({ a: r.value.a, b: r.value.b, type: r.value.type });\n153:         }\n154:       }\n155:     }\n156:   }\n157: \n158:   return { chain, conflicts, reinforcements, clusters, inferred };\n159: }\n160: \n161: function getPairsWithoutEdge(nodes: MemoryNode[], edgeMap: Map<string, RelationshipType>): Array<[MemoryNode, MemoryNode]> {\n162:   const pairs: Array<[MemoryNode, MemoryNode]> = [];\n163:   // Limit to avoid O(n^2) explosion — cap at first 6 nodes (15 pairs max)\n164:   const subset = nodes.slice(0, 6);\n165:   for (let i = 0; i < subset.length; i++) {\n166:     for (let j = i + 1; j < subset.length; j++) {\n167:       const a = subset[i]!;\n168:       const b = subset[j]!;\n169:       if (!edgeMap.has(edgeKey(a.id, b.id))) {\n170:         pairs.push([a, b]);\n171:       }\n172:     }\n173:   }\n174:   return pairs;\n175: }\n176: \n177: function buildClusters(db: Database, ids: number[]): MemoryNode[][] {\n178:   if (ids.length === 0) return [];\n179:   const idSet = new Set(ids);\n180:   const adj = new Map<number, Set<number>>();\n181:   for (const id of ids) adj.set(id, new Set());\n182: \n183:   // Single batch query instead of N×getNeighbors calls\n184:   const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n185:   const relations = db.query<{ source: number; target: number }, number[]>(\n186:     `SELECT source_memory_id as source, target_memory_id as target FROM memory_relations\n187:      WHERE source_memory_id IN (${placeholders}) OR target_memory_id IN (${placeholders})`\n188:   ).all(...ids, ...ids);\n189: \n190:   for (const r of relations) {\n191:     if (idSet.has(r.source) && idSet.has(r.target)) {\n192:       adj.get(r.source)!.add(r.target);\n193:       adj.get(r.target)!.add(r.source);\n194:     }\n195:   }\n196: \n197:   const visited = new Set<number>();\n198:   const clusters: MemoryNode[][] = [];\n199: \n200:   for (const id of ids) {\n201:     if (visited.has(id)) continue;\n202:     const cluster: MemoryNode[] = [];\n203:     const q = [id];\n204:     while (q.length > 0) {\n205:       const cur = q.pop()!;\n206:       if (visited.has(cur)) continue;\n207:       visited.add(cur);\n208:       const node = getMemoryNode(db, cur);\n209:       if (node) cluster.push(node);\n210:       for (const neighbor of adj.get(cur) ?? []) {\n211:         if (!visited.has(neighbor)) q.push(neighbor);\n212:       }\n213:     }\n214:     if (cluster.length > 0) clusters.push(cluster);\n215:   }\n216: \n217:   return clusters;\n218: }\n219: \n220: /**\n221:  * Build a human-readable reasoning context block (max 5 bullets).\n222:  * Suitable for injecting into session context.\n223:  */\n224: export function buildReasoningContext(result: TraversalResult): string {\n225:   const lines: string[] = [];\n226: \n227:   if (result.chain.length > 1) {\n228:     const chainSnippet = result.chain\n229:       .slice(0, 4)\n230:       .map(n => n.content.substring(0, 50).replace(/\\n/g, \" \"))\n231:       .join(\" → \");\n232:     lines.push(`[Chain] ${chainSnippet}`);\n233:   }\n234: \n235:   for (const c of result.conflicts.slice(0, 2)) {\n236:     const a = c.a.content.substring(0, 40).replace(/\\n/g, \" \");\n237:     const b = c.b.content.substring(0, 40).replace(/\\n/g, \" \");\n238:     lines.push(`[Conflict] \"${a}\" ↔ \"${b}\" — verify before applying`);\n239:   }\n240: \n\n(Showing lines 1-240 of 268. Use offset=241 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * graph.ts — Graph traversal engine for LTM reasoning.\n * BFS from a seed memory, up to configurable depth.\n * Detects conflicts, reinforcements, and infers implicit edges via LLM.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { getDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport type { Memory, RelationshipType } from \"./db.js\";\n\nexport interface MemoryNode {\n  id: number;\n  content: string;\n  category: string;\n  importance: number;\n  project_scope: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryPair {\n  a: MemoryNode;\n  b: MemoryNode;","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts","text":"/**\n * graph.ts — Graph traversal engine for LTM reasoning.\n * BFS from a seed memory, up to configurable depth.\n * Detects conflicts, reinforcements, and infers implicit edges via LLM.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { getDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport type { Memory, RelationshipType } from \"./db.js\";\n\nexport interface MemoryNode {\n  id: number;\n  content: string;\n  category: string;\n  importance: number;\n  project_scope: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryPair {\n  a: MemoryNode;\n  b: MemoryNode;\n  type: RelationshipType;\n}\n\nexport interface InferredRelation {\n  a: MemoryNode;\n  b: MemoryNode;\n  type: RelationshipType;\n  persisted: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface TraversalResult {\n  chain: MemoryNode[];\n  conflicts: MemoryPair[];\n  reinforcements: MemoryPair[];\n  clusters: MemoryNode[][];\n  inferred: InferredRelation[];\n}\n\nconst CONFLICT_TYPES = new Set<RelationshipType>([\"contradicts\", \"supersedes\"]);\nconst REINFORCE_TYPES = new Set<RelationshipType>([\"supports\", \"refines\"]);\n\nfunction edgeKey(a: number, b: number): string {\n  return `${Math.min(a, b)}:${Math.max(a, b)}`;\n}\n\ninterface EdgeRow {\n  neighbor_id: number;\n  relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n}\n\nfunction getNeighbors(db: Database, id: number): EdgeRow[] {\n  return db.query<EdgeRow, [number, number]>(\n    `SELECT target_memory_id as neighbor_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE source_memory_id=?\n     UNION ALL\n     SELECT source_memory_id as neighbor_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE target_memory_id=?`\n  ).all(id, id);\n}\n\nfunction getMemoryNode(db: Database, id: number): MemoryNode | null {\n  return db.query<MemoryNode, [number]>(\n    `SELECT id, content, category, importance, project_scope FROM memories WHERE id=? AND status='active'`\n  ).get(id) ?? null;\n}\n\n/**\n * BFS traversal from startId up to depth hops.\n * Returns ordered chain (BFS order), plus pairs classified by edge type.\n */\nexport async function traverseGraph(\n  startId: number,\n  depth = 2,\n  inferImplicit = false,\n): Promise<TraversalResult> {\n  const db = getDb();\n\n  const seedNode = getMemoryNode(db, startId);\n  if (!seedNode) {\n    return { chain: [], conflicts: [], reinforcements: [], clusters: [], inferred: [] };\n  }\n\n  const visited = new Set<number>([startId]);\n  const chain: MemoryNode[] = [seedNode];\n  const conflicts: MemoryPair[] = [];\n  const reinforcements: MemoryPair[] = [];\n\n  // BFS queue: [nodeId, depth]\n  const queue: Array<[number, number]> = [[startId, 0]];\n\n  const edgeMap = new Map<string, RelationshipType>(); // \"a:b\" -> type\n\n  while (queue.length > 0) {\n    const [curId, curDepth] = queue.shift()!;\n    if (curDepth >= depth) continue;\n\n    const curNode = getMemoryNode(db, curId);\n    if (!curNode) continue;\n\n    const neighbors = getNeighbors(db, curId);\n    for (const edge of neighbors) {\n      const neighborNode = getMemoryNode(db, edge.neighbor_id);\n      if (!neighborNode) continue;\n\n      edgeMap.set(edgeKey(curId, edge.neighbor_id), edge.relationship_type);\n\n      if (CONFLICT_TYPES.has(edge.relationship_type)) {\n        conflicts.push({ a: curNode, b: neighborNode, type: edge.relationship_type });\n      } else if (REINFORCE_TYPES.has(edge.relationship_type)) {\n        reinforcements.push({ a: curNode, b: neighborNode, type: edge.relationship_type });\n      }\n\n      if (!visited.has(edge.neighbor_id)) {\n        visited.add(edge.neighbor_id);\n        chain.push(neighborNode);\n        queue.push([edge.neighbor_id, curDepth + 1]);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Build connected components (clusters) from visited nodes\n  const clusters = buildClusters(db, [...visited]);\n\n  // Optionally infer implicit edges between visited nodes that lack a direct edge\n  const inferred: InferredRelation[] = [];\n  if (inferImplicit && chain.length >= 2) {\n    const { classifyRelation } = await import(\"./embeddings.js\");\n    const { relate } = await import(\"./db.js\");\n\n    const pairs = getPairsWithoutEdge(chain, edgeMap);\n    const results = await Promise.allSettled(\n      pairs.map(async ([a, b]) => {\n        const relType = await classifyRelation(a.content, b.content);\n        if (!relType) return null;\n\n        let persisted = false;\n        try {\n          relate({ source_id: a.id, target_id: b.id, relationship_type: relType });\n          persisted = true;\n        } catch {\n          // Memory deleted between traversal and relate — ignore\n        }\n\n        return { a, b, type: relType as RelationshipType, persisted };\n      })\n    );\n\n    for (const r of results) {\n      if (r.status === \"fulfilled\" && r.value) {\n        inferred.push(r.value);\n        if (CONFLICT_TYPES.has(r.value.type)) {\n          conflicts.push({ a: r.value.a, b: r.value.b, type: r.value.type });\n        } else if (REINFORCE_TYPES.has(r.value.type)) {\n          reinforcements.push({ a: r.value.a, b: r.value.b, type: r.value.type });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { chain, conflicts, reinforcements, clusters, inferred };\n}\n\nfunction getPairsWithoutEdge(nodes: MemoryNode[], edgeMap: Map<string, RelationshipType>): Array<[MemoryNode, MemoryNode]> {\n  const pairs: Array<[MemoryNode, MemoryNode]> = [];\n  // Limit to avoid O(n^2) explosion — cap at first 6 nodes (15 pairs max)\n  const subset = nodes.slice(0, 6);\n  for (let i = 0; i < subset.length; i++) {\n    for (let j = i + 1; j < subset.length; j++) {\n      const a = subset[i]!;\n      const b = subset[j]!;\n      if (!edgeMap.has(edgeKey(a.id, b.id))) {\n        pairs.push([a, b]);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return pairs;\n}\n\nfunction buildClusters(db: Database, ids: number[]): MemoryNode[][] {\n  if (ids.length === 0) return [];\n  const idSet = new Set(ids);\n  const adj = new Map<number, Set<number>>();\n  for (const id of ids) adj.set(id, new Set());\n\n  // Single batch query instead of N×getNeighbors calls\n  const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n  const relations = db.query<{ source: number; target: number }, number[]>(\n    `SELECT source_memory_id as source, target_memory_id as target FROM memory_relations\n     WHERE source_memory_id IN (${placeholders}) OR target_memory_id IN (${placeholders})`\n  ).all(...ids, ...ids);\n\n  for (const r of relations) {\n    if (idSet.has(r.source) && idSet.has(r.target)) {\n      adj.get(r.source)!.add(r.target);\n      adj.get(r.target)!.add(r.source);\n    }\n  }\n\n  const visited = new Set<number>();\n  const clusters: MemoryNode[][] = [];\n\n  for (const id of ids) {\n    if (visited.has(id)) continue;\n    const cluster: MemoryNode[] = [];\n    const q = [id];\n    while (q.length > 0) {\n      const cur = q.pop()!;\n      if (visited.has(cur)) continue;\n      visited.add(cur);\n      const node = getMemoryNode(db, cur);\n      if (node) cluster.push(node);\n      for (const neighbor of adj.get(cur) ?? []) {\n        if (!visited.has(neighbor)) q.push(neighbor);\n      }\n    }\n    if (cluster.length > 0) clusters.push(cluster);\n  }\n\n  return clusters;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build a human-readable reasoning context block (max 5 bullets).\n * Suitable for injecting into session context.\n */\nexport function buildReasoningContext(result: TraversalResult): string {\n  const lines: string[] = [];\n\n  if (result.chain.length > 1) {\n    const chainSnippet = result.chain\n      .slice(0, 4)\n      .map(n => n.content.substring(0, 50).replace(/\\n/g, \" \"))\n      .join(\" → \");\n    lines.push(`[Chain] ${chainSnippet}`);\n  }\n\n  for (const c of result.conflicts.slice(0, 2)) {\n    const a = c.a.content.substring(0, 40).replace(/\\n/g, \" \");\n    const b = c.b.content.substring(0, 40).replace(/\\n/g, \" \");\n    lines.push(`[Conflict] \"${a}\" ↔ \"${b}\" — verify before applying`);\n  }\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":240,"totalLines":268,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts","time":{"start":1780925315979,"end":1780925316005}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e488819193e3c1d78d69ccba"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbb5f001oL64XDIYgCEuSQ","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316010,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OVxI2bteQRpYrZVIZqeyAuqu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n3:  * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n4:  */\n5: import type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\n6: import { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\n7: import { join } from \"path\";\n8: import { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\n9: import { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\n10: import { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\n11: import { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\n12: import { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\n13: import { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\n14: import type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\n15: import type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\n16: import { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n17: \n18: export { DB_PATH };\n19: /** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\n20: let DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");\n21: \n22: export function configureDocs(dir: string): void { DOCS_DIR = dir; }\n23: \n24: export function configureCore(config: LtmCoreConfig): void {\n25:   configureDb(config);\n26:   if (config.docsDir) DOCS_DIR = config.docsDir;\n27: }\n28: \n29: export type MemoryCategory = \"preference\" | \"architecture\" | \"gotcha\" | \"pattern\" | \"workflow\" | \"constraint\";\n30: export type RelationshipType = \"supports\" | \"contradicts\" | \"refines\" | \"depends_on\" | \"related_to\" | \"supersedes\";\n31: \n32: export interface Memory {\n33:   id: number;\n34:   content: string;\n35:   category: MemoryCategory;\n36:   importance: number;\n37:   confidence: number;\n38:   source: string | null;\n39:   project_scope: string | null;\n40:   dedup_key: string | null;\n41:   created_at: string;\n42:   last_confirmed_at: string;\n43:   last_used_at: string;\n44:   confirm_count: number;\n45:   status: \"active\" | \"pending\" | \"deprecated\" | \"superseded\";\n46:   first_recalled_at?: string;\n47:   last_recalled_at?: string;\n48:   recall_count?: number;\n49:   superseded_by?: number;\n50:   superseded_at?: string;\n51:   workspace_id?: string;\n52:   agent_id?: string;\n53:   decay_score?: number;\n54: }\n55: \n56: export interface MemoryRelation {\n57:   id: number;\n58:   source_memory_id: number;\n59:   target_memory_id: number;\n60:   relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n61:   created_at: string;\n62: }\n63: \n64: export interface MemoryWithRelations extends Memory {\n65:   tags: string[];\n66:   relations: Array<{ memory: Memory; relationship_type: RelationshipType; direction: \"outgoing\" | \"incoming\" }>;\n67:   /** Populated only when recall({ includeProvenance: true }) is requested. */\n68:   provenance?: import(\"./dao/types.js\").ProvenanceRow[];\n69:   /** Score breakdown + temperature — always populated by recall(). */\n70:   explainer?: import(\"./recall/explainer.js\").RecallExplainer;\n71: }\n72: \n73: export interface LearnInput {\n74:   content: string;\n75:   /** Short human-readable label (≤60 chars). Agent-supplied; falls back to heuristic. */\n76:   title?: string;\n77:   category: MemoryCategory;\n78:   importance?: number;\n79:   confidence?: number;\n80:   source?: string;\n81:   project_scope?: string;\n82:   workspace_id?: string;\n83:   agent_id?: string;\n84:   tags?: string[];\n85:   relate_to?: Array<{ id: number; relationship_type: RelationshipType }>;\n86:   /** Skip regenerating docs/memory-long-term.md (use during bulk imports) */\n87:   skipExport?: boolean;\n88:   /** Audit/provenance — all optional; safe to omit from existing callers. */\n89:   actor?: string;\n90:   sessionId?: string;\n91:   provenanceSourceType?: ProvenanceSourceType;\n92:   provenanceSourceRef?: string;\n93:   provenanceMetadata?: string;\n94: }\n95: \n96: export interface LearnResult {\n97:   action: \"created\" | \"reinforced\";\n98:   id: number;\n99:   confirm_count: number;\n100: }\n101: \n102: export interface RecallInput {\n103:   since?: string;\n104:   until?: string;\n105:   sort_by?: \"relevance\" | \"created\" | \"last_recalled\" | \"recall_count\";\n106: \n107:   query?: string;\n108:   tags?: string[];\n109:   category?: MemoryCategory;\n110:   project?: string;\n111:   limit?: number;\n112:   workspace_id?: string;\n113:   agent_id?: string;\n114:   /** When true, each result includes a `provenance` array. Off by default to preserve latency. */\n115:   includeProvenance?: boolean;\n116: }\n117: \n118: \n119: /** Derive a short title from content when none is agent-supplied. */\n120: export function deriveTitle(content: string): string {\n121:   const trimmed = content.trim();\n122:   const dot = trimmed.indexOf('.');\n123:   const nl = trimmed.indexOf('\\n');\n124:   const boundary = [dot, nl].filter(i => i > 1 && i <= 60).sort((a, b) => a - b)[0];\n125:   if (boundary !== undefined) return trimmed.slice(0, boundary).trim();\n126:   if (trimmed.length <= 60) return trimmed;\n127:   const cut = trimmed.slice(0, 57);\n128:   const lastSpace = cut.lastIndexOf(' ');\n129:   return (lastSpace > 20 ? cut.slice(0, lastSpace) : cut) + '…';\n130: }\n131: \n132: function tryAudit(fn: () => void): void {\n133:   try { fn(); } catch (e) { process.stderr.write(`[audit] write failed: ${e}\\n`); }\n134: }\n135: \n136: function upsertTag(db: Database, name: string): number {\n137:   db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO tags (name) VALUES (?)`, [name]);\n138:   return db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(name)!.id;\n139: }\n140: \n141: function attachTags(db: Database, memoryId: number, tags: string[]): void {\n142:   for (const tag of tags) {\n143:     const tagId = upsertTag(db, tag.toLowerCase().trim());\n144:     db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO memory_tags (memory_id, tag_id) VALUES (?, ?)`, [memoryId, tagId]);\n145:   }\n146: }\n147: \n148: /** Fetch tags for a single memory — used in recall() results. */\n149: function getTagsForMemory(db: Database, memoryId: number): string[] {\n150:   return db.query<{ name: string }, [number]>(\n151:     `SELECT t.name FROM tags t JOIN memory_tags mt ON t.id=mt.tag_id WHERE mt.memory_id=?`\n152:   ).all(memoryId).map(r => r.name);\n153: }\n154: \n155: /** Batch-fetch tags for many memories — used in exportMarkdown to avoid N+1. */\n156: function getTagsBatch(db: Database, ids: number[]): Map<number, string[]> {\n157:   if (ids.length === 0) return new Map();\n158:   const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n159:   const rows = db.query<{ memory_id: number; name: string }, number[]>(\n160:     `SELECT mt.memory_id, t.name FROM memory_tags mt JOIN tags t ON t.id=mt.tag_id\n161:      WHERE mt.memory_id IN (${placeholders})`\n162:   ).all(...ids);\n163:   const result = new Map<number, string[]>();\n164:   for (const r of rows) {\n165:     if (!result.has(r.memory_id)) result.set(r.memory_id, []);\n166:     result.get(r.memory_id)!.push(r.name);\n167:   }\n168:   return result;\n169: }\n170: \n171: function getRelationsForMemory(db: Database, memoryId: number): MemoryWithRelations[\"relations\"] {\n172:   const outgoing = db.query<{ target_memory_id: number; relationship_type: string }, [number]>(\n173:     `SELECT target_memory_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE source_memory_id=?`\n174:   ).all(memoryId);\n175: \n176:   const incoming = db.query<{ source_memory_id: number; relationship_type: string }, [number]>(\n177:     `SELECT source_memory_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE target_memory_id=?`\n178:   ).all(memoryId);\n179: \n180:   const results: MemoryWithRelations[\"relations\"] = [];\n181: \n182:   for (const r of outgoing) {\n183:     const mem = db.query<Memory, [number]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(r.target_memory_id);\n184:     if (mem) results.push({ memory: mem, relationship_type: r.relationship_type as RelationshipType, direction: \"outgoing\" });\n185:   }\n186:   for (const r of incoming) {\n187:     const mem = db.query<Memory, [number]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(r.source_memory_id);\n188:     if (mem) results.push({ memory: mem, relationship_type: r.relationship_type as RelationshipType, direction: \"incoming\" });\n189:   }\n190: \n191:   return results;\n192: }\n193: \n194: function enrichMemory(db: Database, mem: Memory): MemoryWithRelations {\n195:   return { ...mem, tags: getTagsForMemory(db, mem.id), relations: getRelationsForMemory(db, mem.id) };\n196: }\n197: \n198: // --- Decay / relevance scoring ---\n199: \n200: /** Half-life in days by importance level. Infinity = never decays. */\n201: const HALF_LIVES: Record<number, number> = {\n202:   5: Infinity,\n203:   4: 180,\n204:   3: 90,\n205:   2: 30,\n206:   1: 14,\n207: };\n208: \n209: /** Memories below this score are soft-deprecated (not deleted). */\n210: const DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD = 0.25;\n211: \n212: /**\n213:  * Compute effective relevance score.\n214:  * score = importance × confidence × decay\n215:  * decay = 0.5 ^ (days_since / half_life)  (1.0 for importance=5)\n216:  */\n217: export function computeDecayScore(memory: Memory): number {\n218:   const halfLife = HALF_LIVES[memory.importance] ?? 90;\n219:   if (halfLife === Infinity) {\n220:     return memory.importance * memory.confidence;\n221:   }\n222:   const latestTs = [memory.last_used_at, memory.last_confirmed_at, memory.created_at]\n223:     .map(t => new Date(t).getTime())\n224:     .reduce((a, b) => Math.max(a, b), 0);\n225:   const daysSince = (Date.now() - latestTs) / 86_400_000;\n226:   const decay = Math.pow(0.5, daysSince / halfLife);\n227:   return memory.importance * memory.confidence * decay;\n228: }\n229: \n230: /** Update last_used_at for a batch of memory IDs. */\n231: export function updateLastUsed(ids: number[]): void {\n232:   if (ids.length === 0) return;\n233:   const db = getDb();\n234:   const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n235:   db.run(\n236:     `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now') WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n237:     ids\n238:   );\n239: }\n240: \n241: export interface DecayResult {\n242:   deprecated: number;\n243:   scored: number;\n244: }\n245: \n246: /**\n247:  * Compute decay scores for all active memories. Deprecate those below threshold.\n248:  * Protection: importance=5 OR confirm_count>=5 are never deprecated.\n249:  */\n250: export function decayMemories(): DecayResult {\n251:   const db = getDb();\n252: \n253:   const rows = db.query<Memory, []>(\n254:     `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE status = 'active'`\n255:   ).all();\n256: \n257:   const toDeprecate = rows\n258:     .filter(mem => mem.importance !== 5 && mem.confirm_count < 5)\n259:     .filter(mem => computeDecayScore(mem) < DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD)\n260:     .map(mem => mem.id);\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 780. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\nimport { join } from \"path\";\nimport { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\nimport { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\nimport { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\nimport { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\nimport type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\nimport type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\nimport { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n\nexport { DB_PATH };\n/** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\nlet DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","text":"/**\n * db.ts — Global long-term memory (learned insights, patterns, preferences)\n * Replaces skills/learned/*.md with structured SQLite + FTS5.\n */\nimport type { Database } from \"bun:sqlite\";\nimport { existsSync, mkdirSync, writeFileSync } from \"fs\";\nimport { join } from \"path\";\nimport { normalizeKey } from \"./dedup.js\";\nimport { getDb, DB_PATH, configure as configureDb } from \"./shared-db.js\";\nimport { enqueueEmbedding } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { notifyLtm, notifyMemoryAdded } from \"./events/index.js\";\nimport { scrubSecrets } from \"./secretsScrubber.js\";\nimport { insertProvenance, insertAudit, snapshotMemory, listProvenanceBatch } from \"./dao/provenanceAudit.js\";\nimport type { ProvenanceSourceType } from \"./dao/types.js\";\nimport type { LtmCoreConfig } from \"./adapterTypes.js\";\nimport { tmpdir } from \"os\";\n\nexport { DB_PATH };\n/** Adapters can override via configureDocs() or LtmCoreConfig.docsDir. */\nlet DOCS_DIR = join(tmpdir(), \"ltm-docs\");\n\nexport function configureDocs(dir: string): void { DOCS_DIR = dir; }\n\nexport function configureCore(config: LtmCoreConfig): void {\n  configureDb(config);\n  if (config.docsDir) DOCS_DIR = config.docsDir;\n}\n\nexport type MemoryCategory = \"preference\" | \"architecture\" | \"gotcha\" | \"pattern\" | \"workflow\" | \"constraint\";\nexport type RelationshipType = \"supports\" | \"contradicts\" | \"refines\" | \"depends_on\" | \"related_to\" | \"supersedes\";\n\nexport interface Memory {\n  id: number;\n  content: string;\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  importance: number;\n  confidence: number;\n  source: string | null;\n  project_scope: string | null;\n  dedup_key: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n  last_confirmed_at: string;\n  last_used_at: string;\n  confirm_count: number;\n  status: \"active\" | \"pending\" | \"deprecated\" | \"superseded\";\n  first_recalled_at?: string;\n  last_recalled_at?: string;\n  recall_count?: number;\n  superseded_by?: number;\n  superseded_at?: string;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  decay_score?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryRelation {\n  id: number;\n  source_memory_id: number;\n  target_memory_id: number;\n  relationship_type: RelationshipType;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface MemoryWithRelations extends Memory {\n  tags: string[];\n  relations: Array<{ memory: Memory; relationship_type: RelationshipType; direction: \"outgoing\" | \"incoming\" }>;\n  /** Populated only when recall({ includeProvenance: true }) is requested. */\n  provenance?: import(\"./dao/types.js\").ProvenanceRow[];\n  /** Score breakdown + temperature — always populated by recall(). */\n  explainer?: import(\"./recall/explainer.js\").RecallExplainer;\n}\n\nexport interface LearnInput {\n  content: string;\n  /** Short human-readable label (≤60 chars). Agent-supplied; falls back to heuristic. */\n  title?: string;\n  category: MemoryCategory;\n  importance?: number;\n  confidence?: number;\n  source?: string;\n  project_scope?: string;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  relate_to?: Array<{ id: number; relationship_type: RelationshipType }>;\n  /** Skip regenerating docs/memory-long-term.md (use during bulk imports) */\n  skipExport?: boolean;\n  /** Audit/provenance — all optional; safe to omit from existing callers. */\n  actor?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  provenanceSourceType?: ProvenanceSourceType;\n  provenanceSourceRef?: string;\n  provenanceMetadata?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface LearnResult {\n  action: \"created\" | \"reinforced\";\n  id: number;\n  confirm_count: number;\n}\n\nexport interface RecallInput {\n  since?: string;\n  until?: string;\n  sort_by?: \"relevance\" | \"created\" | \"last_recalled\" | \"recall_count\";\n\n  query?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  category?: MemoryCategory;\n  project?: string;\n  limit?: number;\n  workspace_id?: string;\n  agent_id?: string;\n  /** When true, each result includes a `provenance` array. Off by default to preserve latency. */\n  includeProvenance?: boolean;\n}\n\n\n/** Derive a short title from content when none is agent-supplied. */\nexport function deriveTitle(content: string): string {\n  const trimmed = content.trim();\n  const dot = trimmed.indexOf('.');\n  const nl = trimmed.indexOf('\\n');\n  const boundary = [dot, nl].filter(i => i > 1 && i <= 60).sort((a, b) => a - b)[0];\n  if (boundary !== undefined) return trimmed.slice(0, boundary).trim();\n  if (trimmed.length <= 60) return trimmed;\n  const cut = trimmed.slice(0, 57);\n  const lastSpace = cut.lastIndexOf(' ');\n  return (lastSpace > 20 ? cut.slice(0, lastSpace) : cut) + '…';\n}\n\nfunction tryAudit(fn: () => void): void {\n  try { fn(); } catch (e) { process.stderr.write(`[audit] write failed: ${e}\\n`); }\n}\n\nfunction upsertTag(db: Database, name: string): number {\n  db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO tags (name) VALUES (?)`, [name]);\n  return db.query<{ id: number }, [string]>(`SELECT id FROM tags WHERE name=?`).get(name)!.id;\n}\n\nfunction attachTags(db: Database, memoryId: number, tags: string[]): void {\n  for (const tag of tags) {\n    const tagId = upsertTag(db, tag.toLowerCase().trim());\n    db.run(`INSERT OR IGNORE INTO memory_tags (memory_id, tag_id) VALUES (?, ?)`, [memoryId, tagId]);\n  }\n}\n\n/** Fetch tags for a single memory — used in recall() results. */\nfunction getTagsForMemory(db: Database, memoryId: number): string[] {\n  return db.query<{ name: string }, [number]>(\n    `SELECT t.name FROM tags t JOIN memory_tags mt ON t.id=mt.tag_id WHERE mt.memory_id=?`\n  ).all(memoryId).map(r => r.name);\n}\n\n/** Batch-fetch tags for many memories — used in exportMarkdown to avoid N+1. */\nfunction getTagsBatch(db: Database, ids: number[]): Map<number, string[]> {\n  if (ids.length === 0) return new Map();\n  const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n  const rows = db.query<{ memory_id: number; name: string }, number[]>(\n    `SELECT mt.memory_id, t.name FROM memory_tags mt JOIN tags t ON t.id=mt.tag_id\n     WHERE mt.memory_id IN (${placeholders})`\n  ).all(...ids);\n  const result = new Map<number, string[]>();\n  for (const r of rows) {\n    if (!result.has(r.memory_id)) result.set(r.memory_id, []);\n    result.get(r.memory_id)!.push(r.name);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\nfunction getRelationsForMemory(db: Database, memoryId: number): MemoryWithRelations[\"relations\"] {\n  const outgoing = db.query<{ target_memory_id: number; relationship_type: string }, [number]>(\n    `SELECT target_memory_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE source_memory_id=?`\n  ).all(memoryId);\n\n  const incoming = db.query<{ source_memory_id: number; relationship_type: string }, [number]>(\n    `SELECT source_memory_id, relationship_type FROM memory_relations WHERE target_memory_id=?`\n  ).all(memoryId);\n\n  const results: MemoryWithRelations[\"relations\"] = [];\n\n  for (const r of outgoing) {\n    const mem = db.query<Memory, [number]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(r.target_memory_id);\n    if (mem) results.push({ memory: mem, relationship_type: r.relationship_type as RelationshipType, direction: \"outgoing\" });\n  }\n  for (const r of incoming) {\n    const mem = db.query<Memory, [number]>(`SELECT * FROM memories WHERE id=?`).get(r.source_memory_id);\n    if (mem) results.push({ memory: mem, relationship_type: r.relationship_type as RelationshipType, direction: \"incoming\" });\n  }\n\n  return results;\n}\n\nfunction enrichMemory(db: Database, mem: Memory): MemoryWithRelations {\n  return { ...mem, tags: getTagsForMemory(db, mem.id), relations: getRelationsForMemory(db, mem.id) };\n}\n\n// --- Decay / relevance scoring ---\n\n/** Half-life in days by importance level. Infinity = never decays. */\nconst HALF_LIVES: Record<number, number> = {\n  5: Infinity,\n  4: 180,\n  3: 90,\n  2: 30,\n  1: 14,\n};\n\n/** Memories below this score are soft-deprecated (not deleted). */\nconst DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD = 0.25;\n\n/**\n * Compute effective relevance score.\n * score = importance × confidence × decay\n * decay = 0.5 ^ (days_since / half_life)  (1.0 for importance=5)\n */\nexport function computeDecayScore(memory: Memory): number {\n  const halfLife = HALF_LIVES[memory.importance] ?? 90;\n  if (halfLife === Infinity) {\n    return memory.importance * memory.confidence;\n  }\n  const latestTs = [memory.last_used_at, memory.last_confirmed_at, memory.created_at]\n    .map(t => new Date(t).getTime())\n    .reduce((a, b) => Math.max(a, b), 0);\n  const daysSince = (Date.now() - latestTs) / 86_400_000;\n  const decay = Math.pow(0.5, daysSince / halfLife);\n  return memory.importance * memory.confidence * decay;\n}\n\n/** Update last_used_at for a batch of memory IDs. */\nexport function updateLastUsed(ids: number[]): void {\n  if (ids.length === 0) return;\n  const db = getDb();\n  const placeholders = ids.map(() => \"?\").join(\",\");\n  db.run(\n    `UPDATE memories SET last_used_at = datetime('now') WHERE id IN (${placeholders})`,\n    ids\n  );\n}\n\nexport interface DecayResult {\n  deprecated: number;\n  scored: number;\n}\n\n/**\n * Compute decay scores for all active memories. Deprecate those below threshold.\n * Protection: importance=5 OR confirm_count>=5 are never deprecated.\n */\nexport function decayMemories(): DecayResult {\n  const db = getDb();\n\n  const rows = db.query<Memory, []>(\n    `SELECT * FROM memories WHERE status = 'active'`\n  ).all();\n\n  const toDeprecate = rows\n    .filter(mem => mem.importance !== 5 && mem.confirm_count < 5)\n    .filter(mem => computeDecayScore(mem) < DEPRECATION_THRESHOLD)\n    .map(mem => mem.id);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":780,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts","time":{"start":1780925315983,"end":1780925316008}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e498819192bf61bbe54a92f7"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbb8c001eFtM0wtwfVHWu4","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316079,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UUJpXBEwSar3gPo1m0SPxYhO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/src/cluster.ts","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/src/cluster.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /**\n2:  * cluster.ts — Label Propagation community detection for LTM graph nodes.\n3:  */\n4: import type { Cluster, GraphNode, GraphLink } from './graph-app/lib/types.js';\n5: \n6: export type { Cluster };\n7: \n8: /** Label Propagation Algorithm — up to 20 iterations */\n9: export function detectCommunities(nodes: GraphNode[], edges: GraphLink[]): Map<number, string> {\n10:   const labels = new Map<number, number>();\n11:   nodes.forEach(n => labels.set(n.id, n.id));\n12: \n13:   const adj = new Map<number, number[]>();\n14:   nodes.forEach(n => adj.set(n.id, []));\n15:   edges.forEach(e => {\n16:     const src = typeof e.source === 'object' ? (e.source as GraphNode).id : (e.source as number);\n17:     const tgt = typeof e.target === 'object' ? (e.target as GraphNode).id : (e.target as number);\n18:     adj.get(src)?.push(tgt);\n19:     adj.get(tgt)?.push(src);\n20:   });\n21: \n22:   for (let iter = 0; iter < 20; iter++) {\n23:     let changed = false;\n24:     // Fisher-Yates shuffle — single allocation per iteration\n25:     const nodeOrder = [...nodes];\n26:     for (let i = nodeOrder.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {\n27:       const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));\n28:       [nodeOrder[i], nodeOrder[j]] = [nodeOrder[j]!, nodeOrder[i]!];\n29:     }\n30:     for (const node of nodeOrder) {\n31:       const neighbors = adj.get(node.id) ?? [];\n32:       if (neighbors.length === 0) continue;\n33:       const freq = new Map<number, number>();\n34:       for (const nb of neighbors) {\n35:         const lbl = labels.get(nb) ?? nb;\n36:         freq.set(lbl, (freq.get(lbl) ?? 0) + 1);\n37:       }\n38:       let maxCount = 0;\n39:       let bestLabel = labels.get(node.id) ?? node.id;\n40:       for (const [lbl, cnt] of freq) {\n41:         if (cnt > maxCount) { maxCount = cnt; bestLabel = lbl; }\n42:       }\n43:       if (bestLabel !== labels.get(node.id)) {\n44:         labels.set(node.id, bestLabel);\n45:         changed = true;\n46:       }\n47:     }\n48:     if (!changed) break;\n49:   }\n50: \n51:   const labelToCluster = new Map<number, string>();\n52:   let clusterIdx = 0;\n53:   const result = new Map<number, string>();\n54:   for (const [nodeId, lbl] of labels) {\n55:     if (!labelToCluster.has(lbl)) {\n56:       labelToCluster.set(lbl, `cluster-${clusterIdx++}`);\n57:     }\n58:     result.set(nodeId, labelToCluster.get(lbl)!);\n59:   }\n60:   return result;\n61: }\n62: \n63: /** Pick top-3 tags across nodes in the cluster as a label */\n64: export function generateClusterLabel(tags: string[][], fallback: string): string {\n65:   const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n66:   for (const tagList of tags) {\n67:     // Deduplicate per-node tags to avoid inflating frequency for duplicate entries\n68:     for (const tag of new Set(tagList)) {\n69:       freq.set(tag, (freq.get(tag) ?? 0) + 1);\n70:     }\n71:   }\n72:   const sorted = [...freq.entries()].sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]);\n73:   const top = sorted.slice(0, 3).map(([t]) => t);\n74:   return top.length > 0 ? top.join(' · ') : fallback;\n75: }\n76: \n77: /** Assign evenly-distributed HSL colors for N clusters */\n78: export function assignClusterColors(count: number): string[] {\n79:   return Array.from({ length: count }, (_, i) => {\n80:     const hue = Math.round((i / count) * 360);\n81:     return `hsl(${hue}, 65%, 55%)`;\n82:   });\n83: }\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * cluster.ts — Label Propagation community detection for LTM graph nodes.\n */\nimport type { Cluster, GraphNode, GraphLink } from './graph-app/lib/types.js';\n\nexport type { Cluster };\n\n/** Label Propagation Algorithm — up to 20 iterations */\nexport function detectCommunities(nodes: GraphNode[], edges: GraphLink[]): Map<number, string> {\n  const labels = new Map<number, number>();\n  nodes.forEach(n => labels.set(n.id, n.id));\n\n  const adj = new Map<number, number[]>();\n  nodes.forEach(n => adj.set(n.id, []));\n  edges.forEach(e => {\n    const src = typeof e.source === 'object' ? (e.source as GraphNode).id : (e.source as number);\n    const tgt = typeof e.target === 'object' ? (e.target as GraphNode).id : (e.target as number);\n    adj.get(src)?.push(tgt);\n    adj.get(tgt)?.push(src);\n  });","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/src/cluster.ts","text":"/**\n * cluster.ts — Label Propagation community detection for LTM graph nodes.\n */\nimport type { Cluster, GraphNode, GraphLink } from './graph-app/lib/types.js';\n\nexport type { Cluster };\n\n/** Label Propagation Algorithm — up to 20 iterations */\nexport function detectCommunities(nodes: GraphNode[], edges: GraphLink[]): Map<number, string> {\n  const labels = new Map<number, number>();\n  nodes.forEach(n => labels.set(n.id, n.id));\n\n  const adj = new Map<number, number[]>();\n  nodes.forEach(n => adj.set(n.id, []));\n  edges.forEach(e => {\n    const src = typeof e.source === 'object' ? (e.source as GraphNode).id : (e.source as number);\n    const tgt = typeof e.target === 'object' ? (e.target as GraphNode).id : (e.target as number);\n    adj.get(src)?.push(tgt);\n    adj.get(tgt)?.push(src);\n  });\n\n  for (let iter = 0; iter < 20; iter++) {\n    let changed = false;\n    // Fisher-Yates shuffle — single allocation per iteration\n    const nodeOrder = [...nodes];\n    for (let i = nodeOrder.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {\n      const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));\n      [nodeOrder[i], nodeOrder[j]] = [nodeOrder[j]!, nodeOrder[i]!];\n    }\n    for (const node of nodeOrder) {\n      const neighbors = adj.get(node.id) ?? [];\n      if (neighbors.length === 0) continue;\n      const freq = new Map<number, number>();\n      for (const nb of neighbors) {\n        const lbl = labels.get(nb) ?? nb;\n        freq.set(lbl, (freq.get(lbl) ?? 0) + 1);\n      }\n      let maxCount = 0;\n      let bestLabel = labels.get(node.id) ?? node.id;\n      for (const [lbl, cnt] of freq) {\n        if (cnt > maxCount) { maxCount = cnt; bestLabel = lbl; }\n      }\n      if (bestLabel !== labels.get(node.id)) {\n        labels.set(node.id, bestLabel);\n        changed = true;\n      }\n    }\n    if (!changed) break;\n  }\n\n  const labelToCluster = new Map<number, string>();\n  let clusterIdx = 0;\n  const result = new Map<number, string>();\n  for (const [nodeId, lbl] of labels) {\n    if (!labelToCluster.has(lbl)) {\n      labelToCluster.set(lbl, `cluster-${clusterIdx++}`);\n    }\n    result.set(nodeId, labelToCluster.get(lbl)!);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\n/** Pick top-3 tags across nodes in the cluster as a label */\nexport function generateClusterLabel(tags: string[][], fallback: string): string {\n  const freq = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const tagList of tags) {\n    // Deduplicate per-node tags to avoid inflating frequency for duplicate entries\n    for (const tag of new Set(tagList)) {\n      freq.set(tag, (freq.get(tag) ?? 0) + 1);\n    }\n  }\n  const sorted = [...freq.entries()].sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]);\n  const top = sorted.slice(0, 3).map(([t]) => t);\n  return top.length > 0 ? top.join(' · ') : fallback;\n}\n\n/** Assign evenly-distributed HSL colors for N clusters */\nexport function assignClusterColors(count: number): string[] {\n  return Array.from({ length: count }, (_, i) => {\n    const hue = Math.round((i / count) * 360);\n    return `hsl(${hue}, 65%, 55%)`;\n  });\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":83,"totalLines":83,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/src/cluster.ts","time":{"start":1780925316048,"end":1780925316072}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4ac8191b499e75a150bd6e3"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbb96001O2tXU6b7PZyQNx","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316082,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UBGo1ZbP2tQRqvMHaG9MvmcN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/005_clusters.sql","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/005_clusters.sql</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_clusters (\n2:   id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n3:   label TEXT NOT NULL,\n4:   color TEXT NOT NULL,\n5:   node_ids TEXT NOT NULL,\n6:   created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n7:   updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n8: );\n9: \n10: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS cluster_overrides (\n11:   id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n12:   cluster_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n13:   action TEXT NOT NULL,\n14:   payload TEXT NOT NULL,\n15:   created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n16: );\n\n(End of file - total 16 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_clusters (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  label TEXT NOT NULL,\n  color TEXT NOT NULL,\n  node_ids TEXT NOT NULL,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS cluster_overrides (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  cluster_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  payload TEXT NOT NULL,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/005_clusters.sql","text":"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_clusters (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  label TEXT NOT NULL,\n  color TEXT NOT NULL,\n  node_ids TEXT NOT NULL,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS cluster_overrides (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  cluster_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  action TEXT NOT NULL,\n  payload TEXT NOT NULL,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":16,"totalLines":16,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/005_clusters.sql","time":{"start":1780925316053,"end":1780925316075}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4b4819195f72754871f5ce1"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbbd2001Aud3e5F627tXS7","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316082,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uVOl3JrK7OUlgXgY6alveGjF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/016_memory_layout.sql","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/016_memory_layout.sql</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: -- Migration 016: per-view layout persistence\n2: -- Positions are saved only when the user explicitly drags or pins a node.\n3: -- 'view' = 'global' for the global graph, or a project name for drill-down.\n4: \n5: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_layout (\n6:   memory_id  INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES memories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n7:   view       TEXT    NOT NULL,\n8:   x          REAL    NOT NULL,\n9:   y          REAL    NOT NULL,\n10:   pinned     INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n11:   updated_at TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n12:   PRIMARY KEY (memory_id, view)\n13: );\n14: \n15: CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_layout_view ON memory_layout(view);\n\n(End of file - total 15 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"-- Migration 016: per-view layout persistence\n-- Positions are saved only when the user explicitly drags or pins a node.\n-- 'view' = 'global' for the global graph, or a project name for drill-down.\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_layout (\n  memory_id  INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES memories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  view       TEXT    NOT NULL,\n  x          REAL    NOT NULL,\n  y          REAL    NOT NULL,\n  pinned     INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  PRIMARY KEY (memory_id, view)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_layout_view ON memory_layout(view);","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/016_memory_layout.sql","text":"-- Migration 016: per-view layout persistence\n-- Positions are saved only when the user explicitly drags or pins a node.\n-- 'view' = 'global' for the global graph, or a project name for drill-down.\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS memory_layout (\n  memory_id  INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES memories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n  view       TEXT    NOT NULL,\n  x          REAL    NOT NULL,\n  y          REAL    NOT NULL,\n  pinned     INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  updated_at TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  PRIMARY KEY (memory_id, view)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_layout_view ON memory_layout(view);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":15,"totalLines":15,"truncated":false}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/migrations/016_memory_layout.sql","time":{"start":1780925316060,"end":1780925316077}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4bc8191a03262e332be2b78"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbbd7001b0YQ0DPYU3eGC5","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925316085,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_nD6YuKRt4dk8qK6Yk56z08qt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ARCHITECTURE — OpenLTM Plugin\n2: \n3: * **Version:** 1.3 (against plugin v2.9.0)\n4: * **Owner:** Rohi Rikman\n5: * **Status:** Baseline architecture spec; companion to `docs/internal/PRD.md`\n6: * **Last updated:** 2026-06-08\n7: \n8: This document describes the as-built architecture of the OpenLTM plugin, an honest\n9: assessment of its weaknesses, and a target \"magnificent\" architecture with a phased\n10: migration path. It is the reference artifact for the `database-admin` agent (schema work),\n11: the `backend-developer` agent (server / hook work), and the `cloud-architect` agent (any\n12: future sync surfaces).\n13: \n14: The PRD (`docs/internal/PRD.md`) is the contract: §4 (feature inventory) is the as-built ground\n15: truth; §5 (user stories) the acceptance contract; §6 (gaps) the opportunity space this\n16: spec turns into a roadmap.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Table of Contents\n21: \n22: 1. System Context (C4 L1)\n23: 2. Container Diagram (C4 L2)\n24: 3. Component Diagram (C4 L3)\n25: 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n26: 5. Data Model Overview\n27: 6. Architectural Decision Records\n28: 7. Current Architectural Weaknesses\n29: 8. Magnificent Future Architecture\n30: 9. Migration Path\n31: 10. Non-Goals\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 1. System Context (C4 Level 1)\n36: \n37: The LTM plugin is a sidecar process to the Claude Code harness. Everything it does is\n38: local to the developer's machine. There is no cloud dependency, no telemetry, no\n39: multi-tenant store. Two external integration surfaces exist: the MCP protocol (how\n40: Claude talks to the plugin) and Git (read-only, used by the GitLearn skill for backfill).\n41: \n42: ```mermaid\n43: C4Context\n44:   title LTM Plugin — System Context\n45: \n46:   Person(dev, \"Developer\", \"Solo dev, power user, team lead, enterprise dev, or onboarder\")\n47: \n48:   System_Boundary(host, \"Developer Machine\") {\n49:     System(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"CLI / agent runtime; loads plugins, runs hooks, brokers MCP\")\n50:     System(ltm, \"LTM Plugin\", \"Persistent semantic memory, context restore, decay, learn/recall\")\n51:     SystemDb(sqlite, \"openltm.db\", \"Local SQLite (WAL mode) under CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA\")\n52:     System_Ext(git, \"Git Repo\", \"Source of commits for GitLearn backfill\")\n53:     System_Ext(browser, \"Web Browser\", \"Renders graph-app for memory visualization\")\n54:   }\n55: \n56:   Rel(dev, claude, \"Types prompts, runs slash commands\")\n57:   Rel(claude, ltm, \"MCP STDIO + hook stdin/stdout\")\n58:   Rel(ltm, sqlite, \"Reads / writes (WAL)\")\n59:   Rel(ltm, git, \"Reads commit history (read-only)\")\n60:   Rel(dev, browser, \"Opens localhost graph UI\")\n61:   Rel(browser, ltm, \"HTTP to graph-server\")\n62: ```\n63: \n64: **Boundaries**\n65: \n66: - **Inside the boundary:** plugin code, the SQLite DB, the registry JSON, and the\n67:   cache directory the plugin loader reads from. All on the developer's filesystem.\n68: - **Outside:** the Claude Code harness itself (a black box that fires lifecycle events\n69:   and routes MCP calls). The browser, used only for the optional graph UI.\n70: - **Explicitly excluded:** any third-party API. The plugin makes **zero outbound\n71:   network calls** by default. Any future cloud sync (G-I) is opt-in and end-to-end\n72:   encrypted.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 2. Container Diagram (C4 Level 2)\n77: \n78: The plugin decomposes into five runtime containers plus shared on-disk state. The MCP\n79: server is the tool surface; hooks are short-lived processes triggered by lifecycle\n80: events; the graph server is opt-in.\n81: \n82: ```mermaid\n83: C4Container\n84:   title LTM Plugin — Containers\n85: \n86:   Person(dev, \"Developer\")\n87:   System_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\")\n88: \n89:   System_Boundary(ltm, \"LTM Plugin\") {\n90:     Container(mcp, \"MCP Server\", \"Bun + TypeScript, STDIO transport\", \"Long-lived; serves recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph\")\n91:     Container(hooks, \"Hook Runners\", \"Bun scripts invoked by Claude Code\", \"SessionStart, PreCompact, EvaluateSession, UpdateContext\")\n92:     Container(cmds, \"Command + Skill Layer\", \"Markdown specs in commands/ and skills/\", \"Slash commands (/openltm:*), skills (ContinuousLearning, GitLearn, Learned, session-context)\")\n93:     Container(graph, \"Graph Server\", \"Bun HTTP server (opt-in)\", \"Serves graph-app SPA + JSON memory/edge feed\")\n94:     Container(graphapp, \"Graph App\", \"Static SPA served by graph server\", \"Force-directed memory graph viz; Playwright E2E tests\")\n95: \n96:     ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\", \"SQLite WAL\", \"memories, context_items, tags, memory_relations, memories_fts, settings\")\n97:     ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\", \"JSON file under ~/.claude/projects/\", \"cwd → project name mapping\")\n98:     ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\", \"Markdown fallback file\", \"Human-readable context snapshot regenerated on PreCompact\")\n99:   }\n100: \n101:   Rel(dev, claude, \"Prompts, slash commands\")\n102:   Rel(claude, mcp, \"MCP STDIO (JSON-RPC)\")\n103:   Rel(claude, hooks, \"Spawn process, pipe JSON stdin/stdout\")\n104:   Rel(claude, cmds, \"Resolves slash command and skill markdown into prompts\")\n105:   Rel(mcp, db, \"SQL queries (single shared connection)\")\n106:   Rel(hooks, db, \"SQL queries (shared via shared-db.ts)\")\n107:   Rel(hooks, reg, \"Read / write project map\")\n108:   Rel(hooks, summary, \"Regenerate on PreCompact\")\n109:   Rel(dev, graph, \"/openltm:admin server start\")\n110:   Rel(graph, graphapp, \"Serves SPA\")\n111:   Rel(graphapp, graph, \"Fetch /api/memories, /api/relations\")\n112:   Rel(graph, db, \"Read-only queries\")\n113: ```\n114: \n115: **Notes on shared state**\n116: \n117: - A single SQLite connection is held by `shared-db.ts` and reused across MCP server,\n118:   hooks, and graph server within one process. WAL mode permits concurrent readers\n119:   with a single writer; cross-process safety relies on SQLite's file locking.\n120: - `registry.json` is a small JSON map. Concurrent writes are rare (only during\n121:   `/openltm:project register` or `SessionStart` first-touch) but unsynchronised — a\n122:   known weakness called out in §7.\n123: - `context-summary.md` is a write-mostly artifact regenerated by `PreCompact`. It is\n124:   never the source of truth; the DB is.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. Component Diagram (C4 Level 3)\n129: \n130: This level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\n131: components. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\n132: have no internal components.\n133: \n134: ### 3.1 MCP Server components\n135: \n136: ```mermaid\n137: C4Component\n138:   title MCP Server — Components\n139: \n140:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n141:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n142: \n143:   Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n144:     Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n145:     Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n146:     Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n147:     Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n148:     Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n149:     Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n150:     Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n151:     Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n152:   }\n153: \n154:   Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n155:   Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n156:   Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n157:   Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n158:   Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n159:   Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n160:   Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n161:   Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n162:   Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n163:   Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n164:   Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n165:   Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n169: \n170: ```mermaid\n171: C4Component\n172:   title Hook Runners — Components\n173: \n174:   Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n175:   ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n176:   ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n177:   ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n178: \n179:   Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n180:     Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n181:     Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n182:     Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n183:     Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n184:     Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n185:     Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n186:     Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n187:   }\n188: \n189:   Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n190:   Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n191:   Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n192:   Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n193:   Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n194:   Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n195:   Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n196:   Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n197:   Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n198:   Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n199:   Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n200:   Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n201:   Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n202: ```\n203: \n204: **Component responsibilities at a glance**\n205: \n206: | Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n207: |-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n208: | Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n209: | Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n210: | Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n211: | Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n212: | Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n213: | Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n214: | Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n219: \n220: This is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\n221: A \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\n222: compaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n223: \n224: ```mermaid\n225: sequenceDiagram\n226:   autonumber\n227:   actor Dev as Developer\n228:   participant Claude as Claude Code Harness\n229:   participant Start as SessionStart hook\n230:   participant Reg as registry.json\n231:   participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n232:   participant MCP as MCP Server\n233:   participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n234:   participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n235:   participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n236:   participant Sum as context-summary.md\n237: \n238:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n239:   Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n240:   Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n241:   Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n242:   Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n243:   Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n244:   Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n245: \n246:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n247:   Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n248:   Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n249:   MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n250:   alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n251:     MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n252:     MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n253:   end\n254:   MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n255:   MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n256:   Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n257: \n258:   Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n259:   Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n260:   Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 1075. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ARCHITECTURE — OpenLTM Plugin\n\n* **Version:** 1.3 (against plugin v2.9.0)\n* **Owner:** Rohi Rikman\n* **Status:** Baseline architecture spec; companion to `docs/internal/PRD.md`\n* **Last updated:** 2026-06-08\n\nThis document describes the as-built architecture of the OpenLTM plugin, an honest\nassessment of its weaknesses, and a target \"magnificent\" architecture with a phased\nmigration path. It is the reference artifact for the `database-admin` agent (schema work),\nthe `backend-developer` agent (server / hook work), and the `cloud-architect` agent (any\nfuture sync surfaces).\n\nThe PRD (`docs/internal/PRD.md`) is the contract: §4 (feature inventory) is the as-built ground\ntruth; §5 (user stories) the acceptance contract; §6 (gaps) the opportunity space this\nspec turns into a roadmap.\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","text":"# ARCHITECTURE — OpenLTM Plugin\n\n* **Version:** 1.3 (against plugin v2.9.0)\n* **Owner:** Rohi Rikman\n* **Status:** Baseline architecture spec; companion to `docs/internal/PRD.md`\n* **Last updated:** 2026-06-08\n\nThis document describes the as-built architecture of the OpenLTM plugin, an honest\nassessment of its weaknesses, and a target \"magnificent\" architecture with a phased\nmigration path. It is the reference artifact for the `database-admin` agent (schema work),\nthe `backend-developer` agent (server / hook work), and the `cloud-architect` agent (any\nfuture sync surfaces).\n\nThe PRD (`docs/internal/PRD.md`) is the contract: §4 (feature inventory) is the as-built ground\ntruth; §5 (user stories) the acceptance contract; §6 (gaps) the opportunity space this\nspec turns into a roadmap.\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. System Context (C4 L1)\n2. Container Diagram (C4 L2)\n3. Component Diagram (C4 L3)\n4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n5. Data Model Overview\n6. Architectural Decision Records\n7. Current Architectural Weaknesses\n8. Magnificent Future Architecture\n9. Migration Path\n10. Non-Goals\n\n---\n\n## 1. System Context (C4 Level 1)\n\nThe LTM plugin is a sidecar process to the Claude Code harness. Everything it does is\nlocal to the developer's machine. There is no cloud dependency, no telemetry, no\nmulti-tenant store. Two external integration surfaces exist: the MCP protocol (how\nClaude talks to the plugin) and Git (read-only, used by the GitLearn skill for backfill).\n\n```mermaid\nC4Context\n  title LTM Plugin — System Context\n\n  Person(dev, \"Developer\", \"Solo dev, power user, team lead, enterprise dev, or onboarder\")\n\n  System_Boundary(host, \"Developer Machine\") {\n    System(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"CLI / agent runtime; loads plugins, runs hooks, brokers MCP\")\n    System(ltm, \"LTM Plugin\", \"Persistent semantic memory, context restore, decay, learn/recall\")\n    SystemDb(sqlite, \"openltm.db\", \"Local SQLite (WAL mode) under CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA\")\n    System_Ext(git, \"Git Repo\", \"Source of commits for GitLearn backfill\")\n    System_Ext(browser, \"Web Browser\", \"Renders graph-app for memory visualization\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(dev, claude, \"Types prompts, runs slash commands\")\n  Rel(claude, ltm, \"MCP STDIO + hook stdin/stdout\")\n  Rel(ltm, sqlite, \"Reads / writes (WAL)\")\n  Rel(ltm, git, \"Reads commit history (read-only)\")\n  Rel(dev, browser, \"Opens localhost graph UI\")\n  Rel(browser, ltm, \"HTTP to graph-server\")\n```\n\n**Boundaries**\n\n- **Inside the boundary:** plugin code, the SQLite DB, the registry JSON, and the\n  cache directory the plugin loader reads from. All on the developer's filesystem.\n- **Outside:** the Claude Code harness itself (a black box that fires lifecycle events\n  and routes MCP calls). The browser, used only for the optional graph UI.\n- **Explicitly excluded:** any third-party API. The plugin makes **zero outbound\n  network calls** by default. Any future cloud sync (G-I) is opt-in and end-to-end\n  encrypted.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Container Diagram (C4 Level 2)\n\nThe plugin decomposes into five runtime containers plus shared on-disk state. The MCP\nserver is the tool surface; hooks are short-lived processes triggered by lifecycle\nevents; the graph server is opt-in.\n\n```mermaid\nC4Container\n  title LTM Plugin — Containers\n\n  Person(dev, \"Developer\")\n  System_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\")\n\n  System_Boundary(ltm, \"LTM Plugin\") {\n    Container(mcp, \"MCP Server\", \"Bun + TypeScript, STDIO transport\", \"Long-lived; serves recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph\")\n    Container(hooks, \"Hook Runners\", \"Bun scripts invoked by Claude Code\", \"SessionStart, PreCompact, EvaluateSession, UpdateContext\")\n    Container(cmds, \"Command + Skill Layer\", \"Markdown specs in commands/ and skills/\", \"Slash commands (/openltm:*), skills (ContinuousLearning, GitLearn, Learned, session-context)\")\n    Container(graph, \"Graph Server\", \"Bun HTTP server (opt-in)\", \"Serves graph-app SPA + JSON memory/edge feed\")\n    Container(graphapp, \"Graph App\", \"Static SPA served by graph server\", \"Force-directed memory graph viz; Playwright E2E tests\")\n\n    ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\", \"SQLite WAL\", \"memories, context_items, tags, memory_relations, memories_fts, settings\")\n    ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\", \"JSON file under ~/.claude/projects/\", \"cwd → project name mapping\")\n    ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\", \"Markdown fallback file\", \"Human-readable context snapshot regenerated on PreCompact\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(dev, claude, \"Prompts, slash commands\")\n  Rel(claude, mcp, \"MCP STDIO (JSON-RPC)\")\n  Rel(claude, hooks, \"Spawn process, pipe JSON stdin/stdout\")\n  Rel(claude, cmds, \"Resolves slash command and skill markdown into prompts\")\n  Rel(mcp, db, \"SQL queries (single shared connection)\")\n  Rel(hooks, db, \"SQL queries (shared via shared-db.ts)\")\n  Rel(hooks, reg, \"Read / write project map\")\n  Rel(hooks, summary, \"Regenerate on PreCompact\")\n  Rel(dev, graph, \"/openltm:admin server start\")\n  Rel(graph, graphapp, \"Serves SPA\")\n  Rel(graphapp, graph, \"Fetch /api/memories, /api/relations\")\n  Rel(graph, db, \"Read-only queries\")\n```\n\n**Notes on shared state**\n\n- A single SQLite connection is held by `shared-db.ts` and reused across MCP server,\n  hooks, and graph server within one process. WAL mode permits concurrent readers\n  with a single writer; cross-process safety relies on SQLite's file locking.\n- `registry.json` is a small JSON map. Concurrent writes are rare (only during\n  `/openltm:project register` or `SessionStart` first-touch) but unsynchronised — a\n  known weakness called out in §7.\n- `context-summary.md` is a write-mostly artifact regenerated by `PreCompact`. It is\n  never the source of truth; the DB is.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Component Diagram (C4 Level 3)\n\nThis level breaks the **MCP server** and **hook runners** into their internal\ncomponents. The command/skill layer is intentionally not decomposed — markdown specs\nhave no internal components.\n\n### 3.1 MCP Server components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title MCP Server — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"MCP client\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(mcp, \"MCP Server (src/mcp-server.ts)\") {\n    Component(transport, \"STDIO Transport\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/sdk\", \"JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout\")\n    Component(toolreg, \"Tool Registry\", \"McpServer.tool()\", \"Declares recall, learn, forget, relate, context, context_items, graph with Zod schemas\")\n    Component(recall, \"Recall Engine\", \"src/db.ts:recall\", \"FTS5 query → semantic fallback → merge → rank by importance/recency/decay\")\n    Component(learn, \"Learn Engine\", \"src/db.ts:learn\", \"Validate → redact secrets → dedup-key check → insert → return id\")\n    Component(ctxmerge, \"Context Merge\", \"src/db.ts:getContextMerge + src/context.ts:getItems\", \"Build the goal+decisions+progress+gotchas envelope for SessionStart\")\n    Component(graphtrav, \"Graph Traversal\", \"src/graph.ts:traverseGraph\", \"BFS over memory_relations; powers graph and visualization feed\")\n    Component(formatter, \"Compact Formatter\", \"src/mcp-server.ts:compact/strip\", \"Strips embedding blob, truncates content to keep MCP responses small\")\n    Component(config, \"Config Reader\", \"src/config.ts\", \"Reads plugin config; respects mcp.enabled flag\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, transport, \"JSON-RPC\")\n  Rel(transport, toolreg, \"dispatch\")\n  Rel(toolreg, recall, \"recall\")\n  Rel(toolreg, learn, \"learn\")\n  Rel(toolreg, ctxmerge, \"context, context_items\")\n  Rel(toolreg, graphtrav, \"graph\")\n  Rel(toolreg, formatter, \"shape response\")\n  Rel(toolreg, config, \"feature flag check\")\n  Rel(recall, db, \"FTS5 + base table queries\")\n  Rel(learn, db, \"INSERT memories, INSERT memories_fts via trigger\")\n  Rel(ctxmerge, db, \"SELECT context_items + memories\")\n  Rel(graphtrav, db, \"SELECT memory_relations\")\n```\n\n### 3.2 Hook Runners components\n\n```mermaid\nC4Component\n  title Hook Runners — Components\n\n  Container_Ext(claude, \"Claude Code Harness\", \"Spawns hooks per lifecycle event\")\n  ContainerDb(db, \"openltm.db\")\n  ContainerDb(reg, \"registry.json\")\n  ContainerDb(summary, \"context-summary.md\")\n\n  Container_Boundary(hooks, \"Hook Runners (hooks/*.ts)\") {\n    Component(start, \"SessionStart hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Resolve project from cwd → registry; rebuild context-summary.md; emit injection block\")\n    Component(pre, \"PreCompact hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Pull all 4 context types from DB; serialize to context-summary.md (~60 line cap)\")\n    Component(eval, \"EvaluateSession hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Score session; identify candidate insights; (proposes / auto-writes per OQ4)\")\n    Component(update, \"UpdateContext hook\", \"Bun script\", \"Append progress entries; trim to last 20; bump last-touched timestamps\")\n    Component(resolver, \"Project Resolver\", \"shared util\", \"cwd → project name via registry; auto-register on first touch\")\n    Component(injector, \"Context Injector\", \"shared util\", \"Compose ## Restored Project Context block; truncate to ~60 lines + footer\")\n    Component(redact, \"Secret Redactor\", \"shared util\", \"Pattern-match API keys, JWTs, AWS keys; replace with [REDACTED:type]\")\n  }\n\n  Rel(claude, start, \"spawn(SessionStart)\")\n  Rel(claude, pre, \"spawn(PreCompact)\")\n  Rel(claude, eval, \"spawn(EvaluateSession)\")\n  Rel(claude, update, \"spawn(UpdateContext)\")\n  Rel(start, resolver, \"resolve\")\n  Rel(start, injector, \"build block\")\n  Rel(start, db, \"SELECT context_items + globals\")\n  Rel(start, reg, \"read / auto-register\")\n  Rel(pre, db, \"SELECT all context types\")\n  Rel(pre, summary, \"write\")\n  Rel(eval, db, \"INSERT memories (or pending)\")\n  Rel(eval, redact, \"scrub before write\")\n  Rel(update, db, \"INSERT progress; UPDATE timestamps\")\n```\n\n**Component responsibilities at a glance**\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Single source of truth for |\n|-----------|----------------|---------------------------|\n| Recall Engine | Search ranking | Merging FTS5 + semantic results, applying decay |\n| Learn Engine | Write path | Dedup, redaction, importance/category enforcement |\n| Context Merge | Read path for SessionStart | Envelope shape (goal + decisions + progress + gotchas) |\n| Project Resolver | cwd → project | Authoritative map; auto-registration |\n| Secret Redactor | Pattern scrub | Redaction policy, called from learn + EvaluateSession |\n| Context Injector | Format injection | 60-line budget, footer rendering |\n| Compact Formatter | MCP response shaping | Stripping embedding blob, content truncation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Flow: Full Session Lifecycle\n\nThis is the canonical end-to-end flow that ties every container and component together.\nA \"session\" spans from Claude Code launch in a project cwd through to clean exit (or\ncompaction-triggered restart). The diagram shows one full cycle.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n  autonumber\n  actor Dev as Developer\n  participant Claude as Claude Code Harness\n  participant Start as SessionStart hook\n  participant Reg as registry.json\n  participant DB as openltm.db (SQLite)\n  participant MCP as MCP Server\n  participant Eval as EvaluateSession hook\n  participant Pre as PreCompact hook\n  participant Update as UpdateContext hook\n  participant Sum as context-summary.md\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Session start ---\n  Dev->>Claude: cd into project, launch Claude Code\n  Claude->>Start: spawn(SessionStart, stdin=cwd)\n  Start->>Reg: resolve(cwd) → project_name (auto-register if new)\n  Start->>DB: SELECT goal, decisions, gotchas, progress (project) + importance-5 globals\n  Start-->>Claude: stdout = \"## Restored Project Context\\n...\" (≤ 60 lines)\n  Claude-->>Dev: render injected block\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Recall before deciding ---\n  Dev->>Claude: prompt that requires past context\n  Claude->>MCP: recall({ query, project })\n  MCP->>DB: FTS5(MATCH) → ranked rowids\n  alt FTS5 returns < 3 results\n    MCP->>DB: semantic fallback (embedding similarity)\n    MCP->>MCP: merge + dedup by id\n  end\n  MCP->>MCP: apply decay scoring + importance boost\n  MCP-->>Claude: top-N memories (compact, embedding-stripped)\n  Claude-->>Dev: answer informed by recalled context\n\n  Note over Dev,Sum: --- Work + learn ---\n  Dev->>Claude: makes a decision; runs /openltm:memory learn\n  Claude->>MCP: learn({ content, category, importance, project })","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":1075,"truncated":true}},"title":"specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/OpenLtm-main/docs/03-architecture.md","time":{"start":1780925316062,"end":1780925316084}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03564551f2b6160b016a26c383e4c08191b3c6d17f94ce0bf7"}},"id":"prt_ea76bbbdd001s1ZbZej34wXXMl","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","messageID":"msg_ea76b63b4001VeyutJydnMOeDG"}}
