{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780925436295,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"id":"prt_ea76d9183001pip2L46BnIQ7Ox","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"3fe5fca3dda0cb3f2c6aab44594500ad40ef4074","messageID":"msg_ea76d6d61001brZTPTjFoRNDQ7","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":92285,"input":72014,"output":303,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":19968}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780925441022,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"id":"prt_ea76da3fb0014vTutsc3dbZuiU","messageID":"msg_ea76d92b4001YYgbStsLRkq2WN","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","snapshot":"dcf0e57812d3513943fdf083d14de9b3339b39d0","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780925537494,"sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","part":{"id":"prt_ea76ea869001DWDfVr5tkSbci8","messageID":"msg_ea76d92b4001YYgbStsLRkq2WN","sessionID":"ses_158954ac7ffel6uhZW0lvDJ5iU","type":"text","text":"## Mechanism\nOpenLTM defines exactly six relation types in both TypeScript and SQLite: `supports`, `contradicts`, `refines`, `depends_on`, `related_to`, `supersedes` (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:29`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:30`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:95`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:100`). Relations have optional `note` and bounded `weight`, and migration text says effective weight is “base × decay” at read time (`migrations/018_relation_semantics.sql:1`, `migrations/018_relation_semantics.sql:7`). In the inspected traversal path, however, `getNeighbors()` selects only neighbor id and relation type, not weight or note (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:51`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:56`). `relate()` validates source/target existence, then `INSERT OR IGNORE`s only source, target, and type, so it creates but does not update edge metadata (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:587`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:603`).\n\nGraph reasoning is an undirected BFS over `memory_relations`: outgoing and incoming edges are unioned (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:51`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:56`), traversal starts from an active seed and stops at `depth` (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:69`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:93`), and visited nodes are queued once (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:111`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:115`). It classifies `contradicts` and `supersedes` as conflicts, and `supports` and `refines` as reinforcements (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:39`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:40`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:105`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:109`). `depends_on` and `related_to` are traversed but not surfaced as conflict/reinforcement buckets.\n\nImplicit relation inference is bounded: only pairs among the first six visited nodes are considered, capping inference at 15 pairs (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:161`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:164`). If enabled, OpenLTM classifies missing edges and persists them via `relate()` (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:122`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:143`). Separately, `learn()` fire-and-forgets auto-relation detection after embedding, using top-5 similar memories at threshold `0.6` unless `autoRelate` is disabled (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:273`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:284`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:400`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:405`). The classifier can auto-create only `supports`, `contradicts`, `refines`, or `related_to`; `supersedes` and `depends_on` are excluded from auto-inference (`packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:306`, `packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:315`).\n\nOrdinary `recall()` does FTS5 query expansion, optional semantic fallback at similarity threshold `0.5`, filters to `status = 'active'`, enriches rows with direct relations, and returns them; it does not build the BFS conflict summary in the inspected body (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:417`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:462`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:510`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:562`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:584`). Optional context graphing exists via `getContextMergeWithGraph()`: when `ltm.graphReasoning` is enabled, it seeds BFS from two globals plus one scoped memory at depth 2 and emits up to five reasoning lines (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:682`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:702`). Conflict lines explicitly warn “verify before applying” (`packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:235`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:239`). The conflict inspection view also treats only `contradicts` and `supersedes` as conflicts (`migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql:5`, `migrations/004_graph_reasoning.sql:18`). Supersession has schema support via `status='superseded'`, `superseded_by`, and `superseded_at`, but `relate({relationship_type:'supersedes'})` does not itself update those fields (`packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:50`, `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:58`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:587`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:603`).\n\n## Teachings for system-spec-kit\n- **Claim** · Surface contradiction/supersession warnings inline with retrieval/context, not only in graph-debug tools · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:235`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:682` · **Maps-to** · `memory_search` / `memory_context` response envelope · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.84 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Our causal model already has `contradicts`/`supersedes`; the transferable delta is recall-adjacent presentation, not schema.\n- **Claim** · Treat `supersedes` as retrieval suppression/demotion only when coupled to explicit record state · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/schema.sql:50`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:510`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:587` · **Maps-to** · causal-edge write path plus memory-state/archival policy · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · HIGH · **Confidence** · 0.78 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · FSRS decay should not be overridden by a bare edge unless the newer record is verified authoritative.\n- **Claim** · Keep implicit relation inference bounded and shadow-first · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:284`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:161`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:164` · **Maps-to** · `memory_causal_stats` backfill / shadow feedback reducers · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.86 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · The bounds fit local single-user operation, but auto-writing contradictions risks false conflict pollution.\n- **Claim** · Do not add edge `weight` unless traversal/scoring consumes it · **Evidence** · `migrations/018_relation_semantics.sql:2`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:51`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:600` · **Maps-to** · causal-edge strength scoring · **Verdict** · REJECT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.91 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Our causal edges already carry strength; copying an unused metadata column would be dead surface area.\n- **Claim** · Reuse compact conflict copy, not OpenLTM’s separate graph UI machinery · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:224`, `packages/openltm-core/src/graph.ts:248`, `src/cluster.ts:8` · **Maps-to** · response formatter; graph UI as new sub-packet only · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.80 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · A five-line “verify before applying” block improves agent behavior without adding UI/layout state.\n\n## Negative knowledge\nDo not copy `relate()` as-is: `INSERT OR IGNORE` prevents metadata updates and does not enact supersession state.\n\nDo not copy the full cluster/layout subsystem into retrieval: label propagation and pinned coordinates are graph-UI concerns, not continuity quality (`src/cluster.ts:8`, `migrations/016_memory_layout.sql:2`).\n\nDo not assume OpenLTM auto-detects supersession: its classifier excludes `supersedes` and `depends_on` (`packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:306`, `packages/openltm-core/src/embeddings.ts:317`).\n\n## Open questions\nShould system-spec-kit make `contradicts`/`supersedes` checks default in `memory_search`, or only when `includeTrace`/debug profile is enabled?\n\nShould a `supersedes` causal edge automatically change memory state, or require explicit validation evidence first?\n\nCan shadow feedback estimate false-positive contradiction warnings before enabling inline recall blocking?","time":{"start":1780925507689,"end":1780925537491},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_054f64130cf698bf016a26c44378c0819890bba11488435684","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
